reviewText: The quality is very low. The questions are written for a dumb-ass and are mostly blatantly obvious. E.g. the video pauses and the answer is almost always just the last thing that was said. In general you can guess the right answer without having listened at all. Nobody is reviewing my peer-reviewed assignment so it's not letting me complete the course. I am disappointed.

I recently had the opportunity to take the SAP Professional Fundamentals course. I found it to be an invaluable introduction to the world of consulting and the range of skills that are necessary to succeed in this competitive field. I would highly recommend the SAP Professional Fundamentals course to any executive looking to expand their understanding of the consulting industry and the skills necessary to succeed in this field. It provides a solid foundation and is an excellent investment in the professional development of oneself and one's team
